    <h1>Bet&#xAD;ter-fit&#xAD;ting equip&#xAD;ment for SAF sol&#xAD;diers</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201203/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-03"><time>2020-12-03</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>The Sin­ga­pore Army ’s new load-bear­ing sys­tem (LBS) – which con­sists of a belt and a vest – is de­signed to be more er­gonomic than the pre­vi­ous load-bear­ing vest (right) and to im­prove heat dis­si­pa­tion by 30 per cent. Sol­diers re­ceive one of two vari­ants of the LBS, de­pend­ing on the mis­sions they are ex­pected to un­der­take. A new hel­met was also show­cased re­cently.</p>

